The paper deals with the problem of packing circles into a square container, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The paper also presents an algorithm for an online setting, which involves making decisions without knowledge of future inputs, and this is a common theme in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions an upper bound on the packing problem, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
